        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Define the DocumentContent schema — the core container for parsed document content: a tree structure of text nodes and a list of tables. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Document content data model — structure and tables. \par \b Input\/ \:  None (standalone model, references TreeNode and Table). \par \b Output\/ \:  Pydantic BaseModel <computeroutput>DocumentContent</computeroutput> with structure (TreeNode) and tables (List[Table]). \par \b Links\/ \:  [USES_API(7): pydantic.BaseModel; READS_DATA_FROM(8): TreeNode, Table] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>structure is always a valid TreeNode (root of document tree).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>tables list may be empty but never None. \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why separate structure from tables? A: Tables have fundamentally different layout (grid vs. tree). Separating them allows specialized rendering and querying. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Initial creation with semantic markup] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
<para>CLASS 10[Document content container — tree + tables] =&gt; DocumentContent \par \b Use Cases\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>[DocumentContent]: APIResponseBuilder =&gt; SerializeContent =&gt; ReturnParsedDocumentJSON </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
